All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddAppointment
    Controller class for AddAppointment.fxml.

    Initializes the view with a table showing all appointments currently in the database and with fields for the user to input information for a new appointment.

    Handles input validation and facilitates adding an appointment to the database.
    AddCustomer
    Controller class for AddCustomer.fxml.

    Initializes the view by populating the country combobox with Countries from the database

    Handles input validation and facilitates adding a customer to the database.
    Appointment
    Model class for an Appointment from the database.
    AppointmentReportItem
    Model for a row of data in the Total Appointments by Type report.
    AppointmentsManager
    Manages application CRUD operations for the Appointments table in the database.
    Contact
    Model class for a Contact from the database.
    ContactScheduleReport
    Sub-class extending Report class.

    Reports on the schedules for all contacts in the database.
    ContactScheduleReportItem
    Model for a row of data in the Contact Schedule report.
    ContactsManager
    Manages application CRUD operations for the Contacts table in the database.
    CountriesManager
    Manages application CRUD operations for the Countries table in the database.
    Country
    Class that models the Country data received from the database.
    CountryReportItem
    Class is a model for a row in the table generated by the Customers by Country report.
    Customer
    This class models the Customer data that is retrieved from the mysql database.
    CustomersByCountryReport
    Sub-class extending Report class.

    Reports on the number of customers for every country in the database.
    CustomersManager
    Manages application CRUD operations for the Customers table in the database.
    Dashboard  
    DBUtill
    SQL Database helper class for application.

    Gets connection to the database and keeps reference of the current user.
    FirstLevelDivision
    This class models the First-Level Division data from the database.
    FirstLevelDivisionsManager
    Manages application CRUD operations for the First_Level_Divisions table in the database.
    Login  
    LogInAttempts
    File Output class.
    Main
    Main runnable class extending the Application class.

    Adds Login scene to the application stage.
    Report
    Superclass for creating reports in the application.
    TimeTable
    Class representing a dictionary of time strings.
    TotalAppointmentsByTypeReport
    Sub-class extending Report class.

    Reports on the total number of appointments for every appointment type.
    UpdateAppointment
    Controller class for UpdateAppointment.fxml.

    Initializes the view with a table showing all appointments currently in the database and populates fields with data from an existing appointment from the database.

    Handles input validation and facilitates updating an appointment in the database.
    UpdateCustomer
    Controller class for UpdateCustomer.fxml.

    Initializes the view with fields populated with current data for an existing appointment.

    Handles input validation and facilitates updating a customer in the database.
    User
    User class models user data received from the database.
    UsersManager
    Manages application CRUD operations for the Users table in the database.
